This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video frame interpolation, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of deep convolutional neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The exploration of depth information further suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of contextual information and optical flow also suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of warping and interpolation techniques suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
